 The Federal Airports Authority of Nigeria (FAAN) has identified the man who jumped on the wings of an Azman Air flight, in an attempt to get access to the cabin. Speaking to correspondents at the Mallam Aminu Kano International Airport, Kano on Saturday, FAAN’s Managing Director, Captain Rabiu Yadudu identified the man as “Usman Adamu, a Nigerien in origin and who claimed to reside in Iyana Ipaja.” FAAN had earlier suspended Aviation Security unit heads on duty when the incident occurred. The affected officers are the Airport Chief of Security, Mamman Mohammed Sadiku, International Terminal Security Officer, Oni Adedamola Abiodun, Head of Department Domestic Terminal 2, Owotor Kenneth Okezie and Head of Department Domestic Terminal 1, Badejo Adebowale Ayodele. The post FAAN identifies Man who Jumped on Plane’s Wing at Lagos Airport appeared first on . Source: 36Ng The Federal Airports Authority of Nigeria (FAAN) has identified the man who jumped on the wings of an Azman Air flight, in an attempt to get access to the cabin. Speaking to correspondents at the Mallam Aminu Kano International Airport, Kano on Saturday, FAAN’s Managing Director, Captain Rabiu Yadudu identified… July 21, 2019 In "Entertainment" The Federal Airports Authority of Nigerian (FAAN) has said it has arrested a man who climbed the wings of an Azman Air plane, attempting to enter the cabin, adding that it has suspended the security officers on duty at the time. Otto Orondaam, founder of Slum2School Africa, who shared a… July 20, 2019 In "Entertainment" The Federal Airports Authority of Nigerian (FAAN) has said it has arrested a man who climbed the wings of an Azman Air plane, attempting to enter the cabin, adding that it has suspended the security officers on duty at the time. Otto Orondaam, founder of Slum2School Africa, who shared a… July 20, 2019 In "Entertainment"